during office hours.

00:02:14.290 --> 00:02:16.540
And then a number of
you started asking me

00:02:16.540 --> 00:02:19.000
about modulation of
neurotransmitters, which I'll

00:02:19.000 --> 00:02:21.094
talk about in today's lecture.

00:02:21.094 --> 00:02:22.510
And these are
clearly of interest,

00:02:22.510 --> 00:02:27.220
because many recreational
drugs and medications modulate

00:02:27.220 --> 00:02:29.410
neurotransmitter amounts.

00:02:29.410 --> 00:02:30.770
And that is how they work.

00:02:30.770 --> 00:02:32.320
So for example,
some of you might

00:02:32.320 --> 00:02:37.000
be taking things called SSRIs,
specific serotonin re-uptake

00:02:37.000 --> 00:02:40.030
inhibitors like
Prozac, which make

00:02:40.030 --> 00:02:42.760
you feel less anxious
and better about things.

00:02:42.760 --> 00:02:47.380
And these act by prolonging
serotonin activity,

00:02:47.380 --> 00:02:51.040
by preventing it from being
retaken up into cells.

00:02:51.040 --> 00:02:54.100
And I'll touch on this at
the beginning of the lecture.

00:02:54.100 --> 00:02:55.390
And it takes a while--

00:02:55.390 --> 00:02:56.830
is what I've written here--

00:02:56.830 --> 00:03:00.220
for these medications to start
working, because you're really

00:03:00.220 --> 00:03:04.960
asking for a rearrangement
of the whole synaptic process

00:03:04.960 --> 00:03:08.131
and the synaptic structure,
in order that they can work.

00:03:08.131 --> 00:03:09.130
And here is another one.

00:03:09.130 --> 00:03:10.540
What about amphetamines?

00:03:10.540 --> 00:03:11.890
Are they neurotransmitters?

00:03:11.890 --> 00:03:12.730
No.

00:03:12.730 --> 00:03:15.440
They increase the
release of dopamine,

00:03:15.440 --> 00:03:18.580
which is a neurotransmitter,
and they also

00:03:18.580 --> 00:03:22.380
seem to inhibit re-uptake of
dopamine and serotonin is all.

00:03:22.380 --> 00:03:26.110
I'll talk about re-uptake
very briefly in a moment.

00:03:26.110 --> 00:03:28.390
For many medications, both--

00:03:28.390 --> 00:03:30.970
actually, for many medications,
no matter whether or not

00:03:30.970 --> 00:03:33.400
they affect your brain or
other parts of your body,

00:03:33.400 --> 00:03:38.990
the precise mechanism of
